    {
      "id": "tradeoffs",
      "durationMs": 36500,
      "narration": {
        "text": "Sprite carries position, anchor, rotation, scale, and alpha, plus an axis-aligned bounding box for simple overlap tests. SpriteSheet slices a packed texture into cached frames, AnimatedSprite plays them back, and Scene holds everything in z-order with a camera, so scrolling a level means moving the camera and not repositioning the world."
      },
      "actions": [
        {
